RhinoTourism.com
Pune District, India40 contributions
ISKCON Temple visited just Nov
Nov 2021
ISKCON NVCC (New Vedic Cultural middle) is placed in the less congested place of Kondhwa near Pune. ISKCON NVCC is a temple dedicated to Lord Krishna and Goddess Radha. The temple has lavish green hills in the heritage and provides its visitors with a first-rate ambience. once you input the prayer corridor, you'll be awe-struck through the beautiful idols of Lord Krishna and Goddess Radha. The idols are elegantly adorned with stunning clothes and colorful garlands. The ceilings of the dome and the partitions of the temple are artistically adorned with colourful artwork. The temple homes sports like young people education programmes and Bhagvat Gita analyzing lessons, women and own family empowerment activities, and so on. aside from being the residency of Radha, Krishna and Balaram.
Written 31 January 2022

Nice temple
Dec 2020
There is parking space available but it could be difficult to find a parking spot on heavy rush day. Good thing is its free parking. Before the temple entry there are 4 banquet halls of ISKCON. There is a small garden before the temple. You have to climb some steps to enter the temple. On ground floor there is a meditation centre. Adjacent is Balaji temple. The temple premises is surrounded by tall buildings. One can buy prasadam ( laddu ) at 60rs .
